About Me
Started from a basic hello world program in C++ to developing web apps from scratch, I really came a long way. After graduating from Institute of Technology and Science, I got placed in TCS. Training period helped me to experience latest technologies like Machine Learning and Deep Learning which made me fell in love with Python projects. But on the other side I always wanted to be one of the best UI developers which made me learn ReactJS and full stack by my own. You can find some of the projects under Projects page.

Why Do Cats Like Boxes?

"Cats like boxes because they are cryptic animals; they like to hide," Stephen Zawistowski, science adviser for the American Society for the Prevention of Cruelty to Animals, told Business Insider. "And a box gives them a place of safety and security."

While inside a box, cats feel that they cannot be snuck up on from behind or the side â€” anything that wants to approach them must come directly into their field of vision. In effect, such hiding spaces allow them to watch the world around them without being seen.
